# Rule #1 — IMA summer camp: always deploy (non-negotiable)

This rule **overrides** relying on git-push alone, Vercel auto-deploy lag, or “user can deploy later.”

After **any** edit in this repo that affects production (`index.html`, `success.html`, `api/`, `js/`, `vercel.json`, assets, etc.), you **must** finish the same turn with a **forced CLI production deploy** to **`ima-summer-camp`** (`ima-summer-camp.vercel.app`). Retry on auth/network errors until it succeeds.

From **repo root** (folder that contains `api/` — **not** only `api/`):

```bash
cd /Users/tomrichardson/Downloads/vercel-v2 && VERCEL_ORG_ID=team_PXMrLfQ01zlse3XBsDcaPa3s VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=prj_TJxRFRbKAK4AkYBe8AKL1DoH2k9p npx vercel deploy --prod --yes
```

**Only skip** if the user **explicitly** says not to deploy (e.g. “don’t deploy,” “local only”).

`npx vercel --prod --yes` without those env vars may target a different project; **always** use the command above for summer camp.
